article.description: — Trenton Massner had 21 points as Northwestern State defeated New Orleans 81-73 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Massner carries Northwestern State over New Orleans 81-73
article.linkText: Massner carries Northwestern State over New Orleans 81-73
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- — Trenton Massner had 21 points as Northwestern State defeated New Orleans 81-73 on Wednesday night. Carvell Teasett had 16 points for Northwestern State (4-14, 3-4 Southland Conference). Larry Owens added 16 points and 11 rebounds. Damion Rosser had 17 points and nine rebounds for the Privateers (4-11, 3-4). Jahmel Myers and Derek St. Hilaire added 12 points apiece. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
